The Chronicle Lumbidzani Dima, Chronicle Reporter
GOVERNMENT has invited nominations for deserving Zimbabweans to be awarded the Herbert Wiltshire Pfumaindini Chitepo Commendation Award for Justice and Human Rights. <img class="wp-image-495601 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/04/Herbert-Chitepo.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/04/Herbert-Chitepo.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/04/Herbert-Chitepo-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />  Herbert Wiltshire Pfumaindini Chitepo The award has been named in honour of Cde Chitepo, a distinguished nationalist and lawyer who was killed by a car bomb on March 18, 1975 in Lusaka, Zambia. A school, the Herbert Chitepo Ideological College has already been established in his honour. Previously, only members of the uniformed forces could be conferred with such national awards and honours but the New Dispensation extended the honour to civilians. <img class="alignnone wp-image-621628 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Untitled-131-2.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Untitled-131-2.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Untitled-131-2-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The Herbert Wiltshire Pfumaindini Chitepo Commendation Award for Justice and Human Rights is meant to revive the spirit of humanitarianism and to honour people for their distinguished and consistent pursuit of justice and human rights for the greater good of humanity.  In a statement, the Chief Secretary to the President and Cabinet, Dr Misheck Sibanda said anyone who is distinguished and in consistent pursuit of justice and human rights for the greater good of humanity can be nominated. “The Government of Zimbabwe, therefore, invites nominations of people eligible for conferment of this Award. Note that each nomination should be accompanied by a justification in the form of a brief detailed profile on the achievements for which the individual is deemed deserving of this special recognition and national honour. You may present your nomination in the form of a citation, which will be used when the individual is awarded the special honour or in the form of a relevant document which celebrates and immortalises the achievement for posterity,” read the statement. He said nominees should be undisputed leaders in the sector for which they are to be considered. The closing date for nominations that must be addressed and sent to The Acting Registrar Honours and Awards Private Bag 7700 Causeway Harare or Email: honoursandawards@gta.gov.zw is June 30.